{
  "texts": [
    "Most importantly, we replicate the experimental results of Study 1.",
    "Participants in the treatment in Study 2 reduced belief in their focal conspiracy by 12.3 points more than participants in the control (95% CI [10.07, 14.72], p <.001, d = 0.79; Figure 2B and Table S8), translating into a 19.41% average decrease in belief (versus a 2.94% decrease in the control).",
    "Further demonstrating the robustness of our results, we also replicated our findings in a supplemental study conducted using a sample recruited through the participant supplier Lucid (b = -10.99, 95% CI [-16.09, -5.88], p <.001, d =.53; see SM section 8 and Figure S13), which provides relatively inattentive respondents who mostly do non-academic surveys (39).",
    "Thus, the effect is not unique to attentive and engaged participants from Cloud Connect.",
    "5 belief is greater than 50 for all participants because participants with initial belief below 50 were excluded from the study."
  ]
}